---
title: Chermoula Spiced Halloumi with Bulgur Wheat & Chickpea Tabboulleh
description: A zesty blend of spices and herbs, chermoula is a Moroccan spice traditionally used to season fish and meat. But as you will see, chermoula also works brilliantly in vegetarian dishes like this one, complementing the sweetness of the honey and the freshness of the minty yoghurt dressing. Regardless of the weather outside, this recipe is guaranteed to take you to the warm, sunny climes of Northern Africa.
